ðŸ“Š Summary of Results
1. Morphometric Analysis
DLBCL nuclei were significantly larger and more elongated than ENKTCL nuclei, with increased nuclear area (p < 0.0001), perimeter (p < 0.0001), and eccentricity (p = 0.0052). Circularity showed no significant difference (p = 0.1195). 
Hematoxylin mean optical density was markedly higher in DLBCL (p < 0.0001), indicating stronger staining intensity.

2. Traditional Machine Learning (Clinicopathological + Morphometric Features)
XGBoost achieved:
Accuracy: 0.829
AUC: 0.945
F1-score: 0.829
Precision: 0.810
Recall: 0.850
SHAP analysis revealed age, nuclear area, and nuclear hematoxylin OD mean as the most influential features. These were integrated into the multimodal framework used for deep learning classification.

